<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-831] @Property causes ClassCastException in constructor</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-831</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Define a class in Groovy with:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Property String[] fieldNames = [ &apos;street1&apos;, &apos;street2&apos;, &apos;city&apos;, &apos;state&apos;, &apos;zip&apos;, &apos;country&apos; ];&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;GroovyClassLoader parses this successfully.  However, calling Class.newInstance() will throw ClassCastException from within the Groovy object&apos;s constructor.  Removing that property from the class causes the exception to go away, so I&apos;m certain it is the cause of the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The same problem exists on 1.0-jsr-1 and 1.0-beta-6.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>Windows XP, JDK 1.4.2_08, ASM 1.5.2, BEA WLS 8.1SP3, Tapestry 3.0.3</environment>
